[SN]TITLE[SN]
Chelmsford man admits dog cruelty and assault of council worker

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has admitted beating a dog with a lead and then punching a council worker who challenged him.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
CCTV operators spotted James Gilbert, 32, attacking the dog in Duke Street in Chelmsford city centre on Saturday.
A man in his 20s working for the council challenged Gilbert, who punched him. The man and dog were unhurt.
Gilbert, of Ockelford Avenue, Chelmsford, admitted animal cruelty and assault and was remanded in custody by Chelmsford magistrates on Monday.
He is due to be sentenced on 25 August.
